If you fork this project, please:

  1. Rename your fork so users cannot confuse it with the upstream
     Brandkite project. Pick a new product name, replace the wordmark in
     `src/components/brandkiteLogo.tsx`, the assets in `public/` (logo
     files, favicons, preview images), the `<title>` set in
     `src/routes/__root.tsx`, and any user-visible "Brandkite" strings.
  2. Update the Resend sender address in `convex/auth.ts` to a domain
     you control.
  3. Update or remove the seed data in `convex/seed.ts` (the
     `ADMIN_EMAIL`, `ADMIN_NAME`, and seeded "Brandkite" public company),
     and the contact email in `src/components/BrandStudioPage.tsx`.

You may, of course, keep an attribution like "Based on Brandkite
(https://github.com/yosefserkez/brandkite)" — that is encouraged.

================================================================================
Third-party services
================================================================================

Running Brandkite end-to-end relies on third-party services that each have
their own terms of service. Bringing your own API keys is required:

  - Convex                (backend, database, auth, workflows, vector search)
  - Resend                (transactional email for magic-link auth)
  - OpenRouter            (text generation for brand modules)
  - OpenAI                (text embeddings for logo vector search)
  - Replicate             (image generation + CLIP image embeddings)
  - Firecrawl             (URL scraping for brand context)
  - Cloudflare R2         (asset storage, via @convex-dev/r2)
  - Autumn                (billing / usage metering, optional)
  - Sentry                (error monitoring, optional)
  - Umami                 (analytics, optional — remove the script tag in
                           `src/routes/__root.tsx` if you don't want it)

You are responsible for complying with each provider's terms.
